TY  - JOUR
T1  - On the Failure of the Bootstrap for Matching Estimators
AU  - Abadie, Alberto
AU  - Imbens, Guido W.
Y1  - 2008/11/01
PY  - 2008
DA  - 2008/11/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA6474
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
SP  - 1537
EP  - 1557
VL  - 76
IS  - 6
KW  - Average treatment effects
KW  - bootstrap
KW  - matching
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA6474
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Matching estimators are widely used in empirical economics for the evaluation of programs or treatments. Researchers using matching methods often apply the bootstrap to calculate the standard errors. However, no formal justification has been provided for the use of the bootstrap in this setting. In this article, we show that the standard bootstrap is, in general, not valid for matching estimators, even in the simple case with a single continuous covariate where the estimator is root-N consistent and asymptotically normally distributed with zero asymptotic bias. Valid inferential methods in this setting are the analytic asymptotic variance estimator of Abadie and Imbens (2006a) as well as certain modifications of the standard bootstrap, like the subsampling methods in Politis and Romano (1994).
ER  - 

